    "summary": [
      "In 2025, a decade after the Paris Agreement was signed, global temperatures are dangerously close to the agreed threshold. CO2 emissions reached a record high in 2023 despite expansion of renewable energy. The EU has made progress but Brazil and India lag behind. Fossil fuel companies spend millions on lobbying against climate legislation.",
      "The upcoming COP30 summit in Belém, Brazil will test international resolve to meet the Paris Agreement goals. Renewable energy sector offers optimism with record investments and falling battery storage costs."
