    "summary": [
      "In 2024, global temperatures reached 1.45°C above pre-industrial levels, nearing the dangerous threshold set by the Paris Agreement of 1.5°C. The Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) issued a warning that the window for corrective action is shrinking.",
      "Despite the expansion of renewable energy in countries like Germany, China, and the United States, fossil fuel usage remains at historically high levels.",
      "Brazil, one of the world's top three CO2 emitters, faces international criticism over deforestation in the Amazon, which reached 11,568 km² in 2024 according to Brazil's National Institute for Space Research (INPE)."
    ],
